Federal Premuim carry ammo - full box priced at $28.99
Hornady Critical Defense carry ammo - $24.99 per box of 20 = $1.25 per round * 38 = $47.48

All added up, the retail on the ammo I have is $201.13

title: For Sale:  3 semi auto Astra pistols 9mm, 25 auto, 22 short
postcontent:
ASTRA  600 9mm- $375
. AT THE REQUEST OF THE GERMAN MILITARY, who wanted a smaller pistol than the Astra 400 in 9X19, Astra designed their Model 600 in 1943. Between the 16th of May & 16th of July, 1944, 10,540 Astra 600 pistols were delivered to the German military across the Spanish/French border. Another 28,000 had been purchased but the allied advance in France prevented their delivery. Only the first 10,540 have German acceptance stamps. This particular example is a post-war West German police issue. Only up to serial number 10,500 made it into the Nazi hands, the rest of the Astra 600 contract sat in a Spanish arsenal until the early 1950s when they were sold to the West German police. I've always liked the Astra 600s unique looks. The quality of manufacture is high, as the Spanish were out to impress the German military. The German military were already satisfied customers of Astra, having used the compact model 300, the larger model 400. The Model 600/43 has a tublar design that makes it look like a squirt gun! The Model 600 is the ultimate of the Astra tube design, it started in 1912 with the Campo Giro. The Model 600 is the apex of fit, finish and reliability for Astra pistols. Shooting one is not an experience one soon forgets. All prices firm!

title: For Sale:  WW2 Japanese Type 99 "Last Ditch" Arisaka
postcontent:
It is estimated that this "Last Ditch" Japanese Arisaka Type 99 rifle in 7.7 Japanese caliber was made around the end of 1944 when they were running out of supplies.  (The US Navy had a bad habit of sinking their supply ships!) 

For the collectors out there, here are the details: It's an 8th Series Nagoya with defaced mum and excellent condition wood with original urushi oil finish.  Excellent chrome bore with no rust anywhere.  The receiver and bolt serial numbers match, while the firing pin and safety do not.  The extractor has what appears to be a number, but I can't make it out.  It has the late war wood buttplate with three nails.  I've been making and selling custom reproduction Japanese slings for many years, and the one in the photo (a $45 value) is included as a  bonus!

The price is $260 cash face-to-face in the Jacksonville, FL area only.  Sorry, no shipping or trades as this time as I need the cash to pay for another rifle.  The bayonet in the photos is not included in that price, however I will include it in the deal for an extra $40.  (Go price Japanese bayonets on eBay to find out what a great deal THAT is!)  I have a C&R license so I'll need a copy of the buyer's C&R or FL driver's License info. 

All of these items purchased separately would easily be around $400, so don't miss out on this great deal on a beautiful piece of WW2 history!

Feel free to contact me at william dot russ at comcast dot net with any questions.
